---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import TimeLineElement from "../components/cv/TimeLine.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About" sideBarActiveItemID="cv">
  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">About</div>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-10 text-justify">
    Pantagruel Research is an independent research initiative at the intersection of
    <b>quantitative finance</b>, <b>machine learning</b> and <b>data science</b>.
    Our work focuses on the rigorous application of statistical models and modern AI techniques
    to problems in asset management, derivatives, risk and algorithmic trading —
    with a strong emphasis on mathematical foundations and production-ready implementations.
  </div>

  <!-- ─────────────────────────────── CONTRIBUTOR 1 ─────────────────────────────── -->
  <div class="mb-4 flex items-center gap-5">
    <img
      src="/pantagruel-research/alejandro_prendes.jpeg"
      alt="Alejandro Prendes Cabo"
      class="w-24 h-24 rounded-full object-cover ring-2 ring-primary shrink-0"
    />
    <div>
      <div class="text-2xl font-bold">Alejandro Prendes Cabo</div>
      <div class="text-base opacity-70">Lead Data Scientist · QUANT AI Lab</div>
      <a
        href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/alejandro-prendes-cabo/"
        target="_blank"
        class="text-sm link link-primary"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
      >
        LinkedIn ↗
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-8 text-justify">
    Mathematician and physicist specialized in artificial intelligence. Experienced in advanced
    techniques of classical machine learning and deep learning as well as in the production of
    models and MLOps lifecycle on on-premise and cloud platforms. He has also worked on
    multiagent LLM systems definition and alignment — prompt engineering, fine-tuning and
    techniques to improve safety, compliance, controllability and reliability of AI agents.
    Transversal experience across multiple sectors including macroeconomics, banking regulation,
    markets, business analytics, industrial environments, logistics and customer care.
    Speaker at events such as the <b>Andorra Economic Forum</b> and <b>GenAiA</b>.
  </div>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-2xl w-full font-bold">Education</div>
  </div>

  <div class="time-line-container grid gap-4 mb-8">
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Grado en Matemáticas"
      subtitle="2012 to 2018 at Universidad de Oviedo, Oviedo, Spain"
    />
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Grado en Física"
      subtitle="2012 to 2018 at Universidad de Oviedo, Oviedo, Spain"
    />
  </div>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-2xl w-full font-bold">Experience</div>
  </div>

  <div class="time-line-container mb-8">
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Lead Data Scientist"
      subtitle="From Apr 2022 to Present at QUANT AI Lab, Madrid, Spain"
    >
      Principal data scientist coordinating PoC research at Zara.com. Design, modelling and
      productionisation of advanced machine learning models on e-commerce microservices.
      R&amp;D on emerging AI applications. Design of multiagent architectures based on LLMs.
      Development and deployment of the Zara.com customer-care assistant, live in 60+ countries.
    </TimeLineElement>
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Profesor — IA &amp; Big Data"
      subtitle="From Feb 2025 to Present at Instituto Europeo de Posgrado (IEP)"
    >
      Lecturer on the Master in AI &amp; Big Data: Deep Learning concepts &amp; strategic
      applications, and MLOps &amp; generative-model lifecycle.
    </TimeLineElement>
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Senior Data Scientist"
      subtitle="From Jan 2022 to Apr 2022 at COSENTINO, Madrid, Spain"
    />
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Data Scientist / Data Scientist I+D"
      subtitle="From Sep 2019 to Jan 2022 at Management Solutions, Madrid, Spain"
    >
      Predictive analytics &amp; clustering pipelines with distributed computing (Spark).
      Default-prediction models in fintech, operational &amp; credit-risk mining, regulatory
      capital modelling and internal model validation for G-SIB financial institutions.
    </TimeLineElement>
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Colaborador Data Scientist"
      subtitle="From Oct 2017 to Jun 2019 at AEMet — Agencia Estatal de Meteorología, Oviedo, Spain"
    >
      Machine-learning analysis and mining of AEMET databases. Development of computational
      models for homogenisation of historical meteorological time series in Python.
    </TimeLineElement>
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Co-founder &amp; Quantitative Researcher"
      subtitle="From 2023 to Present at Pantagruel Research"
    >
      Independent research on the application of transformer models, reinforcement learning
      and probabilistic methods to financial time series forecasting, portfolio optimisation
      and algorithmic trading.
    </TimeLineElement>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-2xl w-full font-bold">Certifications</div>
  </div>

  <ul class="list-disc mx-6 mb-8 grid gap-2">
    <li>
      <a href="https://coursera.org/verify/HURY47QNTUP6" target="_blank">
        MLOps: Machine Learning in Production – Coursera / DeepLearning.AI (2021)
      </a>
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="http://coursera.org/verify/USRR47YT4VW2" target="_blank">
        Convolutional Neural Networks – Coursera / DeepLearning.AI (2020)
      </a>
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="https://www.coursera.org/account/accomplishments/certificate/AXHY9J4J9N6S" target="_blank">
        Improving Deep Neural Networks – Coursera / DeepLearning.AI (2020)
      </a>
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="http://coursera.org/verify/A8MGU7E9LLDM" target="_blank">
        Neural Networks and Deep Learning – Coursera / DeepLearning.AI (2020)
      </a>
    </li>
  </ul>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-2xl w-full font-bold">Skills</div>
  </div>

  <ul class="list-disc md:columns-5 columns-2 mx-6 mb-12">
    <li>Python</li>
    <li>PyTorch</li>
    <li>TensorFlow / Keras</li>
    <li>scikit-learn</li>
    <li>Spark / Databricks</li>
    <li>Deep Learning</li>
    <li>MLOps / MLFlow</li>
    <li>LLMs / LangChain</li>
    <li>Docker</li>
    <li>SQL</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="divider"></div>

  <!-- ─────────────────────────────── CONTRIBUTOR 2 ─────────────────────────────── -->
  <div class="mb-4 flex items-center gap-5 mt-4">
    <img
      src="/pantagruel-research/javier_fernandez.jpeg"
      alt="Javier Fernández Sánchez de la Viña"
      class="w-24 h-24 rounded-full object-cover ring-2 ring-primary shrink-0"
    />
    <div>
      <div class="text-2xl font-bold">Javier Fernández Sánchez de la Viña</div>
      <div class="text-base opacity-70">Quant Trader · CFA · University Lecturer</div>
      <a
        href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/javier-fernandez-sanchez-de-la-vina-8082bb176/"
        target="_blank"
        class="text-sm link link-primary"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
      >
        LinkedIn ↗
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-8 text-justify">
    Physicist, mathematician and economist with more than five years of experience as a
    derivatives trader, specialising in volatility products. His professional approach is
    rooted in a triple academic background — BSc programmes in Mathematics, Physics and
    Economics at <b>Universidad de Oviedo</b> — complemented by an <b>MSc in Mathematical
    and Computational Finance</b> from the <b>University of Oxford</b> (Oriel College).
    Currently channelling his passion for financial markets into the academic world, teaching
    at <b>CUNEF Universidad</b>, <b>Universidad de las Hespérides</b> and
    <b>UNIE Universidad</b>, covering subjects such as Machine Learning &amp; Investments,
    Derivatives, Alternative Investments, Quantitative Risk Management and Macroeconomics.
    Previously a quantitative trader at <b>Arfima Trading</b> focused on futures and options
    on indices like SX5E, SPX, V2X and VIX.
  </div>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-2xl w-full font-bold">Education</div>
  </div>

  <div class="time-line-container grid gap-4 mb-8">
    <TimeLineElement
      title="MSc in Mathematical and Computational Finance"
      subtitle="2019 to 2020 at Oriel College, University of Oxford, United Kingdom"
    />
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Bachelor degree in Mathematics (240 ECTS)"
      subtitle="2014 to 2019 at Universidad de Oviedo, Oviedo, Spain"
    />
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Bachelor degree in Physics &amp; Economics"
      subtitle="Universidad de Oviedo, Oviedo, Spain"
    />
  </div>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-2xl w-full font-bold">Experience</div>
  </div>

  <div class="time-line-container mb-8">
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Profesor universitario"
      subtitle="From Feb 2026 to Present at CUNEF Universidad · Universidad de las Hespérides · UNIE Universidad, Madrid, Spain"
    >
      Teaching across multiple institutions: Machine Learning &amp; Investments (CUNEF, Data
      Science Master), Derivatives &amp; Alternative Investments &amp; Quantitative Risk
      Management (Hespérides), and Macroeconomics II (UNIE, Mathematics degree).
    </TimeLineElement>
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Quantitative Trader"
      subtitle="From Oct 2020 to Dec 2025 at Arfima Trading, Madrid, Spain"
    >
      Derivatives trader with special focus on volatility products. Active management of a
      portfolio of futures and options on several underlyings (SX5E, SPX, V2X, VIX).
      Academic research review, data analysis from derivatives pricing to statistical
      modelling, visualisation tools and risk management.
    </TimeLineElement>
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Research Fellow"
      subtitle="From Nov 2018 to Jul 2019 at Universidad de Oviedo, Oviedo, Spain"
    >
      Drug Repurposing through Computational Techniques.
    </TimeLineElement>
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Co-founder &amp; Quantitative Researcher"
      subtitle="From 2023 to Present at Pantagruel Research"
    >
      Research on volatility modelling, derivatives pricing, factor-based portfolio construction
      and the application of machine learning to financial markets. Author of in-depth technical
      articles combining academic rigour with practical implementation.
    </TimeLineElement>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-2xl w-full font-bold">Certifications &amp; Awards</div>
  </div>

  <ul class="list-disc mx-6 mb-8 grid gap-2">
    <li>
      CFA Charterholder – CFA Institute
    </li>
    <li>
      IELTS Academic (7.5 – C1)
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="https://www.coursera.org/account/accomplishments/verify/YQ5L76VNMM5C" target="_blank">
        Social and Economic Networks: Models and Analysis – Coursera (2019)
      </a>
    </li>
    <li>
      Beca de Grado María Cristina Masaveu Peterson (2018)
    </li>
    <li>
      Beca de Excelencia Académica María Cristina Masaveu Peterson (2017)
    </li>
  </ul>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-2xl w-full font-bold">Skills</div>
  </div>

  <ul class="list-disc md:columns-5 columns-2 mx-6 mb-10">
    <li>Python</li>
    <li>R</li>
    <li>Matlab</li>
    <li>Derivatives Pricing</li>
    <li>Volatility Models</li>
    <li>Risk Management</li>
    <li>Portfolio Construction</li>
    <li>Econometrics</li>
    <li>Macro Finance</li>
    <li>Statistical Modelling</li>
  </ul>
</BaseLayout>
